title: Nine Entertainment Sells Talkback Radio Stations To Pub Tycoon Arthur Laundy For $56m | 10 News
description: Nine Entertainment has struck a 56-million-dollar deal with publican powerhouse Arthur Laundy selling its top-rating talkback radio slate - including 2GB, 3AW, 4BC and 6PR.  The move is understood to be part of Nine's digital-leaning strategy, with the family's negotiations led by former Liberal MP Craig Laundy.  The sale is subject to ACCC approval and is expected to be finalised by the end of June. title: Trump Dismisses Claims He Fell Asleep During Cabinet Meeting | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has dismissed claims he fell asleep during a recent cabinet meeting, insisting he was merely closing his eyes because the press conference had become “pretty boring.” Trump said photos circulating online likely caught him mid-blink, adding, “I don’t sleep much.” He also joked that Senator Marco Rubio would have woken him if he had actually dozed off.
